                            <h2 class="flooring-title">POLYUREA FLOORING</h2>
                            <p>
                                Polyurea, a subset of polyurethanes, functions similarly to PU coating on concrete floors. 
                                Formed by an amine-isocyanate reaction, it offers superior resistance to harsh environments and easy curing. 
                                While slightly more expensive than polyurethane, it's ideal for construction, bridges, car parks, and roof repairs. 
